        <!-- AI Capabilities Deep Dive -->
        <section id="ai">
            <h2 class="section-title">AI Capabilities Deep Dive</h2>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem; color: #666; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                The AI architecture and approach fundamentally differentiate these platforms. Bond emphasizes autonomous, agentic AI, while Atlar emphasizes augmented intelligence with transparency and privacy controls.
            </p>

            <!-- Bond Treasury AI -->
            <div class="ai-section">
                <h4>Bond Treasury AI</h4>
                <span class="ai-label">AGENTIC AI ARCHITECTURE</span>

                <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8;">
                    <strong>Core Philosophy:</strong> Bond is built from the ground up on AI foundations. The "AI-native" architecture means AI intelligence spans the entire platform—not bolted onto legacy systems. Agentic AI is deployed to handle treasury operations autonomously with minimal human oversight, operating 24/7.
                </p>

                <div class="subsection-title" style="margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Specific AI Workflows</div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>1. Autonomous Cash Positioning</h5>
                    <p>AI agents gather balances from banks and ERPs, calculate daily positions, factor in incoming and outgoing payments, and provide CFOs real-time liquidity views without spreadsheets or manual intervention.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>2. Intelligent Stress Testing & Auto-Hedging</h5>
                    <p>Background simulations continuously stress-test cash positions, FX exposures, and market scenarios. When thresholds are breached, AI proposes or auto-executes hedging adjustments to protect treasury positions.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>3. Smart Reconciliation</h5>
                    <p>Automated matching and discrepancy identification reduce reconciliation time and eliminate manual errors across multi-entity environments.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>4. Generative AI Insight Agents</h5>
                    <p>AI highlights data patterns, outliers, and anomalies. Provides context-aware recommendations to treasury teams based on historical patterns and market conditions.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>5. Autonomous Risk Monitoring</h5>
                    <p>24/7 counterparty risk assessment, credit exposure monitoring, and automatic alerts. AI continuously monitors credit ratings, market moves, and exposure thresholds without human triggers.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>6. Predictive Forecasting</h5>
                    <p>ML-driven pattern recognition in cash flows with variance analysis. AI learns from historical data to predict future cash positions with increasing accuracy.</p>
                </div>

                <p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #666; font-style: italic; border-top: 1px solid #e0e4e8; padding-top: 1rem;">
                    <strong>AI Maturity Assessment:</strong> Bond claims deep agentic capabilities but provides limited public evidence, case studies, or detailed technical disclosure. The emphasis on "autonomous" and "24/7" operations is compelling but lacks transparency regarding model type, training data, or specific use case validations. No disclosure of data privacy safeguards for customer data used in AI models.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Atlar AI -->
            <div class="ai-section">
                <h4>Atlar Intelligence (AI Layer)</h4>
                <span class="ai-label">AUGMENTED INTELLIGENCE</span>

                <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8;">
                    <strong>Core Philosophy:</strong> Atlar's AI layer is built directly into the platform, combining conversational AI with complete, up-to-date financial data. AI is designed to <strong>augment and accelerate human decision-making</strong> rather than replace it. Focus is on making treasury data instantly accessible and actionable to finance teams.
                </p>

                <div class="subsection-title" style="margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Specific AI Workflows</div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>1. AI-Powered Bank Reconciliation</h5>
                    <p>Automated matching, verification, and closing across all banks and entities. AI-assisted matching prevents mismatches and resolves discrepancies proactively. Reconciliation teams can focus on exceptions rather than routine matching.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>2. Conversational AI Assistant</h5>
                    <p>Natural language queries for treasury data. Users ask questions like "What's our EUR cash position across all entities?" and Atlar consolidates results, analyzes changes, and explains findings in seconds—without building spreadsheets or SQL queries.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>3. ML-Based Cash Flow Forecasting</h5>
                    <p>Multiple forecasting methods available: simple growth adjustments, regression analysis, and machine learning. Turns historical data into adaptive forecasts in seconds. Users can select the right model for their business.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>4. Dynamic Treasury Reporting</h5>
                    <p>AI generates reports instantly and applies the right visualizations automatically. Surfaces insights from variance analysis to cash flow bridges. Reports are contextual and adapted to user role and needs.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>5. Operational Guidance</h5>
                    <p>Contextual AI guidance for reconciling accounts, running payment batches, and connecting new banks. Reduces onboarding friction and accelerates team productivity.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="ai-workflow">
                    <h5>6. Change Detection & Analysis</h5>
                    <p>Automatically detects trends and identifies drivers of financial changes. Provides contextual explanations for why cash positions or forecasts moved—surfacing root causes instantly.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="subsection-title" style="margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">AI Security & Privacy (Atlar Intelligence)</div>
                <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8;">
                    <li><strong>Data Access Control:</strong> AI cannot retrieve data users don't have access to. Respects existing role-based permissions.</li>
                    <li><strong>No Training on Customer Data:</strong> Customer data is NEVER used to train or fine-tune Atlar Intelligence models.</li>
                    <li><strong>EU Data Processing:</strong> All processing runs on AWS in Europe. Customer data never leaves Atlar's environment.</li>
                    <li><strong>Role-Based AI Access:</strong> AI access controls mirror user permissions—admins, not users, define what data AI can query.</li>
                </ul>

                <p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #666; font-style: italic; border-top: 1px solid #e0e4e8; padding-top: 1rem;">
                    <strong>AI Maturity Assessment:</strong> Atlar Intelligence is more transparent about capabilities and limitations. The platform launched AI as a named product with clear use cases. Focus is on practical, day-to-day treasury workflows rather than autonomous operation. Privacy and security are explicitly addressed—a significant advantage for regulated financial institutions. More documented with specific use cases and customer stories.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- AI Workflow Comparison Table -->
